            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At its meeting on February 17, 1949, the National Security Council adopted a
                    report to President Truman reviewing developments in Yugoslavia and recommending
                    a policy of relaxation over export controls to Yugoslavia. The report,
                    designated <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 18/2, was approved by the
                    President the following day.</p>
                <pb facs="0883" n="869" xml:id="pg_869"/>
                <p>The text of the report was not declassified in time to be included in this volume
                    of documents.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
